From: Rusty Russell <rusty@rustcorp.com.au>
Date: Fri, 28 Sep 2012 15:05:14 +0930
Subject: [PATCH] virtio_balloon: not EXPERIMENTAL any more.
Git-commit: 7a23eb28fa645f1f0c2ec38274c11bc78c50c047
References: FATE#314135
Patch-Mainline: v3.7

It is not experimental in any vaguely-sane sense.

Reported-by: Michael S. Tsirkin <mst@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Rusty Russell <rusty@rustcorp.com.au>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/virtio/Kconfig |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/virtio/Kconfig b/drivers/virtio/Kconfig
index e699968..31fc552 100644
--- a/drivers/virtio/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/virtio/Kconfig
@@ -26,8 +26,8 @@ config VIRTIO_PCI
 	  If unsure, say M.
 
 config VIRTIO_BALLOON
-	tristate "Virtio balloon driver (EXPERIMENTAL)"
-	depends on EXPERIMENTAL && VIRTIO
+	tristate "Virtio balloon driver"
+	depends on VIRTIO
 	---help---
 	 This driver supports increasing and decreasing the amount
 	 of memory within a KVM guest.
